{{Refimprove|date=August 2009}} {{Infobox Union|<!-- Please include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. --> |name= STIBYS |country= [[Honduras]] |affiliation= [[Federación Unitaria de Trabajadores de Honduras|FUTH]] |members= |full_name= Union of Beverage and Related Industry Workers |native_name= Sindicato de Trabajadores de la Industria de la Bebida y Similares |image= |founded= |current= |head= [[Carlos Humberto Reyes|Carlos H. Reyes]] |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= |people= |website= http://stibys.blogspot.com/ |footnotes= }} '''Sindicato de Trabajadores de la Industria de la Bebida y Similares''' ([[Spanish language|Spanish]] for ''Union of Beverage and Related Industry Workers'') is a [[trade union]] in [[Honduras]] founded in 1959. It is affiliated to [[FUTH]], a trade union congress, and internationally to the [[IUF]]. STIBYS is working together with other left-wing organizations in the CNRP (National Coordination of Civil Resistance) and has been active in the resistance against the [[2009 Honduran constitutional crisis#Coup_d.27.C3.A9tat|2009 Honduras coup d'état]].
The current general secretary of STIBYS is [[Carlos Humberto Reyes]], who is standing in the [[Honduran general election, 2009|November 2009 elections]] as an independent presidential candidate.<ref name="official_candidate_order">{{cite web| last =| first =| authorlink =| coauthors =| title =Publicación del voto despeja incógnitas| work =| publisher =Tiempo| year =2009| url =http://tiempo.hn/secciones/politica/1956-publicacion-del-voto-despeja-incognitas |format =| doi =| accessdate =2009-08-07 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5irH5p3mA |archivedate=2009-08-07 |deadurl=no|language=es}}</ref><ref name="enlazando_mission090730">{{cite web| last =| first =| authorlink =| coauthors =| title =International Mission denounces the brutal repression of pacific demonstrations| work =| publisher =Agencia Latinoamerica de Información| date =2009-07-30| url =http://www.alainet.org/active/32099 |format =| doi =| accessdate =2009-08-02 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5ijh7EsjY |archivedate=2009-08-02 |deadurl=no}}</ref><ref name="laprensa_reyescandidate">{{cite web| last =| first =| authorlink =| coauthors =| title =Defying threats, Zelaya supporters continue protests| work =| publisher =[[La Prensa (San Antonio)|La Prensa]]| date =2009-07-31| url =http://www.laprensasa.com/2.0/3/309/273599/America-in-English/Defying-threats-Zelaya-supporters-continue-protests.html | doi =| accessdate =2009-08-02 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5ijkLpskf |archivedate=2009-08-02 |deadurl=no}}</ref>
